name: ServiceProvider
definition: party that provides and typically provisions professional services, such as consulting, financial, legal, real estate, education, communications, storage, or processing services, to other parties, typically defined in a service agreement
label: service provider

name: NegotiableCommodity
definition: commodity that can be bought or sold in some marketplace
label: negotiable commodity

name: TransactionConfirmation
label: transaction confirmation
definition: written communication from a seller or service provider reciting the relevant details of a transaction

name: ContractualProduct
explanatoryNote: This represents the case where the product itself is a contract, such as a life insurance policy or financial instrument, rather than a product or service whose terms of use, license to use, or terms of service are specified in a product.
definition: product that takes the form of an agreement
label: contractual product

name: Product
label: product
definition: commercially distributed good that is (1) tangible property, (2) the output or result of a fabrication, manufacturing, or production process, or (3) something that passes through a distribution channel before being consumed or used.
explanatoryNote: Financial products include contracts that are developed via a financial service-specific process, such as a life insurance policy, demand deposit account or financial instrument, for example. Leases and rentals are similar in that they are initiated via some contractual development process, wherein the product is the right to use something for some period of time.

name: Service
definition: intangible activity performed by some party for the benefit of another party
label: service
explanatoryNote: Sometimes services are difficult to identify because they are closely associated with a good; such as the combination of a diagnosis with the administration of a medicine. No transfer of possession or ownership takes place when services are sold, and they (1) cannot be stored or transported, (2) are instantly perishable, and (3) come into existence at the time they are bought and consumed.

name: Sale
label: sale
definition: exchange of goods or services for money

name: TransactionEvent
definition: any sale, assignment, lease, license, loan, advance, contribution, or other transfer of any interest in or right to use any property (tangible or intangible) or money, however that transaction is effected, and regardless of whether the terms of the transaction are formally documented
label: transaction event

name: ClientIdentifier
label: client identifier
definition: sequence of characters uniquely identifying a client within the context of some organization

name: ServiceAgreement
label: service agreement
definition: written contract between a client and service provider whereby the service provider supplies some service in the form of time, effort, and/or expertise in exchange for compensation

name: CustomerIdentifier
definition: sequence of characters uniquely identifying a customer within the context of some organization
label: customer identifier

name: Customer
label: customer
definition: party that receives or consumes products (goods or services) and has the ability to choose between different products and suppliers

name: Buyer
explanatoryNote: A buyer is the party that acquires, or agrees to acquire, ownership (in case of goods), or benefit or usage (in case of rights or services), something in the context of a sale, and may or may not be an end user of the product, good, service, or right.
definition: party that purchases something in exchange for money or other consideration under a contract of sale
label: buyer

name: Producer
definition: grower, maker, fabricator, or manufacturer of some product or other good
label: producer

name: ContractualTemplateProduct
definition: contractual product that is finalized through specification of values for parameters defined in a template
label: contractual template product

name: OffTheShelfProduct
definition: product that is readily available from merchandise in stock, or can be quickly and easily configured to order, not specially designed or custom-made
label: off-the-shelf product

name: ProductIdentifier
label: product identifier
definition: sequence of characters uniquely identifying a product in some context

name: Supplier
definition: party that provides goods or services that some party wants or needs, especially over a long period of time
label: supplier
explanatoryNote: A supplier may be distinguished from a contractor or subcontractor, who commonly adds specialized input to deliverables.

name: Client
definition: party that purchases professional services from, or has a formal relationship to purchase services from another party
label: client

name: CustomProduct
definition: product that is made to order, commissioned based on a customer's specifications
label: custom product

name: Consumer
definition: party that utilizes economic goods or services, typically for personal, family, or household purposes
explanatoryNote: The general notion of a consumer includes an end user, and is not limited to a purchaser, in the distribution chain of a good or service
label: consumer

name: Seller
definition: party that makes, offers or contracts to make a sale to an actual or potential buyer
label: seller

name: Commodity
explanatoryNote: Commodities are most often used as inputs in the production of other goods or services. The quality of a given commodity may differ slightly, but it is essentially uniform across producers.
definition: material resource used in commerce that is interchangeable with other commodities of the same type
label: commodity

name: Good
explanatoryNote: An inherently useful and relatively scarce tangible item produced from agricultural, construction, manufacturing, or mining activities. Off-the-shelf products, including off-the-shelf software products and customization of software products, are generally considered to be goods. Energy, such as electricity, is also considered to be a good from a legal perspective, and meets the criteria of being manufactured or produced via some process, including but not limited to a mining process. According to the UN Convention On Contract For The International Sale Of Goods, the term 'good' does not include (1) items bought for personal use, (2) items bought at an auction or foreclosure sale, (3) aircraft or ocean-going vessels.
label: good
definition: physical, produced item over which ownership rights can be established, whose ownership can be passed from one party to another by engaging in transactions, and that is not money or real estate

name: sellsTo
definition: links a party in the role of broker, dealer, vendor, or merchandiser to a purchaser or potential purchasing party
label: sells to

name: provisions
label: provisions
definition: customizes, provides, or outfits something required for use in delivering a service

name: hasSeller
definition: indicates the vendor in the context of a sales transaction
label: has seller

name: buysFrom
definition: links a party in the role of purchaser to a party from which they have made or are planning to make a purchase
label: buys from

name: sells
definition: links a party in the role of broker, dealer, vendor, or merchandiser to something that they make available for sale
label: sells

name: buys
definition: links a party in the role of purchaser to something that they have purchased or plan to purchase
label: buys

name: supplies
definition: links a party in the role of outfitter, provisioner, distributor, etc. to something that they provide
label: supplies

name: hasBuyer
label: has buyer
definition: indicates the purchasing party in the context of a sales transaction

name: isProvisionedBy
definition: identifies the service provider that provisions the service or facility
label: is provisioned by

name: isSuppliedBy
definition: identifies the party (supplier, vendor, distributor, etc.) that makes a product available
label: is supplied by
